    header("HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request");
    die("SQL injection vulnerability detected");
}

// Allow the user to access the system
header("HTTP/1.1 200 OK");
?>
```
This script checks if the input data contains any malicious SQL code. If it does, it returns a 400 Bad Request response.

4. File Inclusion:
```php
<?php

// Check if the input is valid
if (!isset($_POST['username']) || !isset($_POST['password'])) {
