    header("HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request");
    die("Buffer overflow vulnerability detected");
}

// Allow the user to access the system
header("HTTP/1.1 200 OK");
?>
```
This script checks if the input data is too long and could potentially cause a buffer overflow. If it is, it returns a 400 Bad Request response.

These are just a few examples of common web application vulnerabilities and how you can detect and prevent them in your Softaculous or Aparat system. It's important to regularly review and update your security measures to ensure the safety of your system and users.

